The paper deals with maintaining a minimum vertex cover in a dynamic graph, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GT). The use of a potential function to analyze the algorithm is a technique commonly used in the analysis of dynamic algorithms (cs.DM). The paper also involves approximation algorithms (cs.AL) and complexity theory (cs.CC) in the analysis of the update time.
